{
  "texts": [
    "Education and Information Technologies (2024) 29:14513-14545",
    "The results of our meta-analysis distinctly indicate a significant medium to large effect size of project-based learning on students' creativity capacities (SMD = 0.57, Z = 6.22, P < 0.001).",
    "Through project-based learning, students are often prompted to hone in on problem-solving skills, a process that inherently involves stimulating and harnessing their creativity faculties (Bradley-Levine & Mosier, 2014).",
    "Indeed, innovation is not an instantaneous feat; it is progressively nurtured through cycles of attempts, missteps, and introspection.",
    "Projectbased learning offers an expansive platform for students to both test and extend the horizons of their thought processes, which, in turn, markedly boosts their creativity competencies (Saad & Zainudin, 2022)."
  ]
}